> Hi,
>
> One of my first consulting assignments after graduation in the 1987
> was to convert a medical heart monitor that was written in  PDP-8
> assembly code to run on a PC back then. It was interesting, they will
> still doing their research using a PDP-8 with 1 inch magnetic tape
> even then. I have an estimate, and they thought it was too high, about
> $50,000 for code and new system in  four months. When they took it
> over to another medical company, it actually cost them over $100
> million to do and five years.
>
> In addition, for operating systems class, we wrote a multitasking os
> than ran on a stand-alone PDP-11. It was interesting to see that
> 'fortran.sav' appeared whenerve their was crash. We thought this
> happened because the core operating system used a fortran subsystem.
> (Like the way the HP-9000 used a HP Pascal 3.1 sub system for its OS).
>
> What do you think?
>
> DK
